.TH CBT-UNPACK "1" "February 2026" "cbt-unpack (cbt) 0.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
cbt-unpack \- generically unpack file
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cbt-unpack
\fIARCHIVE\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
Automatically unpacks the provided archive file by consulting the unpack plugins
in the in the $cbtUnpackPlugins directory.
.PP
If a plugin recognizes the provided file it unpacks it and sets the hasUnpacked
environment variable to 1 causing the process to stop. Otherwise, the remaining
available pluins are examined. If no plugin has recognized the file, the process
will fail.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Display help page
.SS "Environment:"
.TP
CBT_UNPACK_PLUGINS
Specify the directory in which unpack plugins can be
found (defaults to: /usr/share/cbt/unpack-plugins)
